Class BotScheduler.MonthSchedule

  • java.lang.Object
    • waffleoRai_cafebotCommands.BotScheduler.MonthSchedule
  • Enclosing class:
    BotScheduler

    public static class BotScheduler.MonthSchedule
extends java.lang.Object
    A wrapper class for a HashMap mapping Day of the Week IDs (int) to DaySchedule type map wrappers, which contain shift information for a given day of the week in that month.

    July 1, 2018
    Version:

    • Method Detail

      • get

        public BotScheduler.DaySchedule get(int day_of_week)
        Get the DaySchedule, the object containing shift information, for the given day of the week.
        Integer correlating to day of the week should be consistent with the Java.util.Calendar value used for that day of the week. Only integers 0-6 are technically valid, though in theory a DaySchedule could be mapped to any integer.
        This method is synchronized to prevent multiple threads from modifying the Map wrapped by this MonthSchedule at the same time.
        Parameters:
        day_of_week - Day of the week to pull the schedule for. Must be an integer between 0-6 inclusive. Integer to day of week correlation is determined by the Java.util.Calendar class.
        Returns:
        The DaySchedule for the requested day of the week, if it has been set. Otherwise, null.

      • put

        public void put(int day_of_week,
                BotScheduler.DaySchedule ds)
        Map a DaySchedule to a day of the week for the month represented by this MonthSchedule.
        Integer correlating to day of the week should be consistent with the Java.util.Calendar value used for that day of the week. Only integers 0-6 are technically valid, though in theory a DaySchedule could be mapped to any integer.
        This method is synchronized to prevent multiple threads from modifying the Map wrapped by this MonthSchedule at the same time.
        Parameters:
        day_of_week - Day of the week to map the schedule to. Must be an integer between 0-6 inclusive. Integer to day of week correlation is determined by the Java.util.Calendar class.
        ds - DaySchedule to map to the requested day of the week.
